03/04/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Austrian authorities are investigating wartime Croatian deputy defence minister, General Vladimir Zagorec and several Austrian nationals for possible money laundering, according to local media reports Monday (April 2nd) Local prosecutors are looking into business operations at the Klagenfurt-based Hypo Alpe Adria bank as well as several other institutions. 
Zagorec, who was responsible for weapons supplies during the 1990s conflicts, was arrested in Vienna last month, on the basis of an international warrant issued by Zagreb. 
Croatia accuses him of misappropriating 3.7m euros in state funds. 
(HINA, HRT, Index.hr - 02/04/07)
